article.headline: Arizona State 68, Santa Clara 63
article.story: TEMPE, Ariz. (AP) -- Another big game from Ike Diogu has given Arizona State its best start in 14 years. Diogu scored 21 points, grabbed 18 rebounds and blocked a career-best seven shots to lead the Sun Devils past Santa Clara 68-63 Wednesday night. Arizona State is 9-1 for the first time since the 1990-91 season after winning its seventh straight game for the first time since 1980-81. "You got to remember that we were picked 10th in this league so that being the case, I'm just glad we are 9-1," Sun Devils coach Rob Evans said. "I'm glad we are winning ballgames, not necessarily blowing anybody away. To me, a one-point win is like a rout." It nearly got away after the Sun Devils opened up a 10-point lead but Santa Clara (7-5) got within 66-63 with 25.4 seconds remaining on Ethan Rhode's 3-pointer. Arizona State made two of four free throws and Bronco Kyle Bailey was called for traveling with 14 seconds left to keep Santa Clara from getting any closer. Diogu shot 7-for-13 from the field and grabbed 17 defensive rebounds as the Sun Devils took advantage of the Broncos' 35 percent field goal shooting (23 of 66). "That's what happens when you don't make baskets," Santa Clara coach Dick Davey said. "You blame some of it on yourself and some of it on the good 'D' and they did a good job defensively." The Broncos missed seven of their first nine shots and never had the lead. Bailey led Santa Clara with 22 points. Travis Niesen added 14. "I've been here and I've experienced highs and lows, losing games because of rebounds so I just tell myself that anything in my vicinity I was going to bring it down," said Diogu, who had his fifth double-double of the season and 20th of his career. "I didn't want to leave anything up to chance." Steve Moore had 12 points and Serge Angounou added 11 for the Sun Devils. Diogu's blocks were one short of a school record and he now has 103 for his career, fifth on the school list. "I am a good shot blocker, I had a lot of blocks in high school, it's just a matter of going up there and getting it," said Diogu. "Seven blocks doesn't surprise me. I am capable of doing those type of things. (I'm) just being alert on help side and helping out my teammates and the rest takes care of itself." "Ike really was a man possessed because he wasn't able to move around like he wanted to move around inside," Evans said. "They were hanging on to him pretty good and had him surrounded. Ike is going to score. If we are not able to get him the basketball, he'll just go get it off the glass and score that way."
